s/2021/06/16111605/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-new-seat-tube-single-piece-design-768x1152.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111605/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-new-seat-tube-single-piece-design-1024x1536.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111605/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-new-seat-tube-single-piece-design-696x1044.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111605/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-new-seat-tube-single-piece-design-1068x1602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111605/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-new-seat-tube-single-piece-design-280x420.jpg 280w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-262075\">The V2.2 is available in four frame sizes with two rocker links covering short, tall, light and heavy riders.</figcaption></figure><p>Altering what is effectively the backbone of the bike, the redesigned seat tube prompted a redesign of almost all of its interfacing parts; the bottom bracket, lower shock mount, rocker link and rocker pivot.&nbsp;</p><figure id=\"attachment_262074\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-262074\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111559/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-frame-shock-ohllins-coil.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111559/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-frame-shock-ohllins-coil.jpg\" alt=\"raaw madonna v2.2 frame shock only ohlins coil\" width=\"1200\" height=\"764\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111559/raaw-madonna-v2-point-2-frame-shock-ohllins-coil.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/16111559/raaw-ma